✅ Step-by-Step — Create Pivot Table (Matrix) in Power BI
Step 1 — Load Data
1.	Open Microsoft Power BI Desktop
2.	Home → Get Data → Excel/CSV
3.	Load your dataset
4.	Click Report View
________________________________________
Step 2 — Add Matrix Visual
1.	From Visualizations pane
2.	Click Matrix icon
3.	Blank matrix appears on report
________________________________________
Step 3 — Set Rows (like Pivot Rows)
Drag a field to Rows
Example:
•	Drag Region → Rows
________________________________________
Step 4 — Set Columns (like Pivot Columns)
Drag a field to Columns
Example:
•	Drag Product → Columns
________________________________________
Step 5 — Set Values (like Pivot Values)
Drag numeric field to Values
Example:
•	Drag Sales → Values
•	It shows Sum of Sales
________________________________________
Step 6 — Format Like Pivot
1.	Click the Matrix
2.	Go to Format pane
3.	Turn ON:
o	Subtotals
o	Grand Totals
o	Row headers
Now it behaves exactly like a Pivot Table.
🎯 Aim
To create a Pivot Table–style report in Microsoft Power BI Desktop using the Matrix visual to analyze sales by Region and Product.
________________________________________
🧭 Algorithm (12 Points)
1.	Open Microsoft Power BI Desktop.
2.	Click Home → Get Data → Excel.
3.	Select the file PowerBI_Pivot_Practice.xlsx and load the data.
4.	Go to Report View.
5.	Click on the Matrix visual from the Visualizations pane.
6.	Drag the Region field into the Rows section.
7.	Drag the Product field into the Columns section.
8.	Drag the Sales field into the Values section.
9.	Ensure the aggregation is set to Sum of Sales.
10.	Enable Subtotals and Grand Totals from the Format pane.
11.	Sort the matrix in descending order based on total sales.
12.	Observe and analyze the pivot-style summary of sales by region and product.

